      <string>&lt;html&gt;&lt;head/&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight:600;&quot;&gt;QShaderViewer in a nutshell:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; -qt-list-indent: 1;&quot;&gt;&lt;li style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Load a geometry file (OBJ). &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Load a vertex shader (GLSL).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Load a fragment shader (GLSL).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;QShaderViewer will work when all 3 files have been loaded.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;After that, you can load files on-the-fly to see how they look in the screen.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight:600;&quot;&gt;Movement instructions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; -qt-list-indent: 1;&quot;&gt;&lt;li style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Drag your mouse on the screen to move the world.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Use your movement keys (←, ↑, →, ↓) and + / - to move the camera.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Use the WASD keys to move the light, and Q or E to move it closer/farther from the model.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;